> Don't be alarmed at the amount of olive oil we're asking you to use … the
> Mediterranean diet is famed for its health benefits, which can be attributed
> to the extensive use of olive oil. It's crazy good for you due to its sky
> high antioxidant levels (found in its phenolic compounds) and omega-9 content.
> Omega-9 is one of the "good fats" everyone speaks of, with a plethora of
> health benefits. Olive oil is 85% good fat so tuck in!!!

== Veg Prep ==

First you can get all your veg prep done! Cut the @Echalion Shallot{2} in half
through the root, peel and then finely chop into ½cm pieces. Peel and grate
the @Garlic Clove{2}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{} if you have one). Cut
the @Courgette{1} in half lengthways, cut each half into four strips
lengthways, then chop the strips into 1cm cubes. Chop the
@Vine Tomatoes{2}(chopped into 1cm cubes). Finely chop the
@Basil{1}(finely chopped) and half the @Wild Rocket{1}(half chopped).

> Tip: Don't worry, there may be a lot of prep, but it's all plain sailing from
> here!

== Pesto ==

Put a #frying pan{} on medium heat (no oil!) and add the @Pine Nuts{40}. Dry
fry them for ~{1%minute}, or until they start to turn golden.

> Tip: Watch them like a hawk or they will burn!

Once golden, tip your pine nuts onto your #chopping board{} and chop them as
finely as you can (don't wash the pan, you'll use it later to dry fry the
courgettes!).

Put your finely chopped basil, rocket and pine nuts in a #bowl{}. Sprinkle in
the @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{3}, a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a good
grind of @black pepper{pinch} and pour in your best quality
@Olive Oil{6%tbsp}. Add a quarter of your grated garlic and mix everything
together thoroughly.

> Tip: If you do happen to have a food processor, you can use it here, but we
> prefer the satisfaction of doing it by hand!

== Tomato Salad ==

Squeeze the @Lemon{1/2}(juiced) juice into another larger bowl and pour in a
good drizzle of olive oil. Add your tomatoes and a quarter of your chopped
shallot. Mix everything together and leave to the side.

== Orzotto ==

Put your remaining chopped shallot in a pan with a drizzle of oil on medium
heat and cook for ~{3-4%minutes}, before adding your remaining garlic and
cooking for ~{1%minute} more. Add the @Orzo{180%g} and stir it around until it
is nicely coated in your garlicky oil, then pour in the @Water{400%ml} and add
the @Vegetable Stock Pot{1}.

Bring to a simmer, stirring to dissolve your stock pot, then turn the heat
down slightly and simmer gently for ~{10%minutes} or until your pasta is 'al
dente' and the liquid has been absorbed.

> Tip: 'Al dente' simply means the pasta is cooked through but has a tiny bit
> of firmness left in the middle.

> Tip: Stir from time to time to ensure it doesn't stick to the bottom of the
> pan!

> Tip: If all the liquid has been absorbed and the orzo is not quite cooked,
> just add a couple of tbsp of water and keep cooking.

== Charred Courgettes and Assembly ==

Whilst your orzo is cooking, put the pan you used for your pine nuts back on
medium heat without any oil. Once the pan is hot, add your courgette cubes and
cook them for ~{7-8%minutes}, turning occasionally until they are charred.
Remove the pan from the heat.

> Tip: If they are not very charred, just leave them cooking for a bit longer.

Once your orzo is cooked, stir through three-quarters of your pesto along with
your charred courgette. Serve in #bowls{} with your remaining rocket, tomato
salad and a spoonful of your extra pesto on top. Enjoy!